:{{A|VO chapter1 4 natasha 213.ogg}} '''Natasha:''' The place you are going to is called Rivet Town. Follow the path through the mountains to the north for a bit and you'll arrive there.
:{{A|VO chapter1 4 natasha 214.ogg}} '''Natasha:''' Let me think... I'm almost out of metal plates and bandages used for immobilizing broken bones. There's a market in the center of Rivet Town. Residents left behind piles of materials there when they evacuated. Please look for some there...
:{{A|VO chapter1 4 natasha 215.ogg}} '''Natasha:''' Oh! Also, rubbing alcohol. I kept a bunch at the orphanage, since the kids often got into tussles. I didn't bring it with me when I left... I hope it's still intact.
:{{A|VO chapter1 4 natasha 216.ogg}} '''Natasha:''' ...Lastly, painkillers. There should be a bunch stored in the old lab. Hopefully they haven't been destroyed by monsters...
:{{A|VO chapter1 4 natasha 217.ogg}} '''Natasha:''' These should be enough to get by for a bit longer. Be careful. Don't push yourselves too hard.
:{{A|VO chapter1 4 seele 213.ogg}} '''Seele:''' Metal plates and bandages, rubbing alcohol, and painkillers... Got it, piece of cake.
:{{A|VO chapter1 4 seele 214.ogg}} '''Seele:''' Let's go, if we leave now we can still make it back before sundown. When it comes to helping injured people groaning in pain, the sooner the better.
----
:{{A|VO chapter1 4 bronya 246.ogg}} '''Bronya:''' If we hadn't happened to be passing by... were you really planning to go into the Fragmentum alone?
:{{A|VO chapter1 4 seele 215.ogg}} '''Seele:''' Of course. What's all the fuss about? I've done that loads of times.
:{{A|VO chapter1 4 bronya 247.ogg}} '''Bronya:''' So reckless... According to the rules of the Silvermane Guards, any expedition into the Fragmentum must have a squad of at least four members, as well as a communications officer.
:{{A|VO chapter1 4 seele 216.ogg}} '''Seele:''' Exactly, a rule of the Silvermane Guards. Don't apply your rules to us.
{{Dialogue End}}

